I am extremely disappointed with the quality of this Natasha Denona eyeshadow palette.
I ordered it as a birthday gift from my husband back in November, but I only opened and started using it at the end of December, on my birthday. The black shade has crumbled badly and is now practically gone. The metallic rusty shade completely fell out of the pan ‚Äî it simply detached. When I tried to pick it up to put it back, it literally crumbled in my fingers. The pan is now completely empty.

I own many palettes from brands like Anastasia Beverly Hills, Tarte, MAC, and Makeup by Mario ‚Äî which I absolutely love ‚Äî and I have never experienced anything like this. Never. This level of quality is a complete failure, especially at this price point

review:
[This review was collected as part of a promotion.] Natasha Denona Eye Sculpt Texture and Tone Palette in Dramatic is my new favorite item in my makeup case! 
The packaging is very nice quality. I'm ecstatic that inside the case there is a gorgeous mirror.
There are 18 shades including neutral tones to velvety black in smoothe matte, as well as 6 glittering shades ready to party for the holidays!
This palette has everything I need in eyeshadow to take me from daytime to playtime! I love how the neutral tones are on the left side of the case and the dramatic deep tones are on the right. 
The kit also includes a two-sided instruction card which demonstrates how to apply the eyeshadows..
The eyeshadow is rich, and goes on so smoothly with little to no fall-out. (I only noticed a tiny bit with the darkest shades). 
I love how well the colors hold up without fading, and how silky they feel on my eyelids.
It's super easy to wash off, which is great for bold shades.
I really appreciate the creativity that this palette from Natasha Denona inspires. I've always appreciated the versatility of neutral shades, but love the attention that rich dramatic  eyeshadow provides. A make-up artist friend taught me the importance and versatility of using a good black eyeshadow, not only for dramatic looks, but also to use to thicken eyelashes after applying mascara, and even to use as an eyeliner!
This Natasha Denona Eye Sculpt Texture and Tone Palette in Dramatic is the best of endless possibilities!

review: I really like this shade of brick red on my neutral - warm undertone, blue eyes auburn hair. It has enough blue undertone to make my eyes pop and enough warmth that I don't look washed out. What I don't love is the misleading 12HR full coverage label ... I've never found any lipstick which stays on for a full 12 hours and this one is very drying because it's matte, so it doesn't do more than stain. If you are 50+ and/or suffer from lipstick bleed, you need to prime this one carefully - otherwise you get red stain and pigment traveling up where you don't want to see it. It does feels comfortable and silky when you apply it but because it dries out so quickly, I need to find the right lip primer for this otherwise fab lipstick. I like the packaging - the tube doesn't pop open in your makeup bag or purse. Match your colour first, then buy with confidence.
